---
description: Sync git before agent work
alwaysApply: true
---

Before reading or editing any file in this repo:

1. Run `git fetch --all --prune`
2. On `main` or `master`: if behind `origin`, run `git pull --ff-only`
3. On a feature branch: after fetch, if `origin/main` has commits not in this branch, merge with `git merge origin/main` (or ask before rebasing)
4. If pull or merge fails (conflicts, dirty tree), stop and report — do not commit on top

Run this at the start of every session and again before any commit or push.
